-- 
Sovereign Funds Preparing to Buy Shares, Independent Reports

-- B y   T i m   B a r w e l l
-- 
2011-09-25T09:46:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-25/sovereign-funds-preparing-to-buy-shares-independent-reports.html
Sovereign wealth funds are
preparing to take advantage of depressed share prices and buy
billions of dollars of equities worldwide, the Independent on
Sunday reported.  The board of the $40-billion Alaska Permanent Fund will
meet Friday to discuss moving from bonds into shares, executive
director Mike Burns told the newspaper, adding that most
sovereign funds are looking at equities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tim Barwell in London on 
 tbarwell@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
